Supplementary description. Male.
LB: 2.62–2.95 (mean, 2.82 ). LR: 0.63–0.79 (mean, 0.73 ). LP: 0.88–0.94 (mean, 0.90 ). N = 5 for all measurements. Male genitalia. Heavily sclerotized. Spiculum gastrale (sternite IX;
Fig. 85
) robust, evidently longer than the penis or its apodeme, bent leftward. Tegmen (
Fig. 84
) with apodeme long and slender, nearly 1.4 times as long as the diameter of the tegminal ring, more or less widened toward the apex. Penis (
Figs. 81–83
) long and very heavily sclerotized, rather thick in profile, more or less moderately curved downward in the basal 1 / 5 , then slightly bent upward in the apical 1 / 5 ; sides slightly broadened from the median 1 / 3 to the base and to the apex, then gradually convergent apically; apical projection (
Fig. 82
) truncate at apex. Basal part of the endophallus (
Fig. 81
) mostly wrapped in penis, with a pair of plate-like sclerites and numerous moderately dense minute spicules in the basal part.

Female. LB: 3.03–3.24 (mean, 3.12 ). LR: 0.70–0.82 (mean, 0.75 ). LP: 1.03–1.04 (mean, 1.04 ). N = 5 for all measurements. Female genitalia. Sternite VIII (
Fig. 86
) with a pair of patches of several minute setae near the apex; arms relatively broad, nearly 0.8 times as long as apodemes, slightly shorter than the coxite and stylus combined, moderately basally fused, and apically arcuate; apodemes slender, moderately divergent near the apex. Coxites (
Fig. 87
) long and slender, nearly four times longer than styli; styli apicolaterally inserted, long and slender, nearly six times longer than wide. Spermatheca (
Fig. 88
) with cornu slender, strongly curved and slightly attenuate; collum weakly convex; ramus indistinct; insertions of the duct and gland relatively close to each other.
